# Pitcrew Lessons Learned
# 
# This file is automatically appended to every mechanic prompt.
# When a pit stop encounters a problem, the crew chief adds a lesson here.
# Each lesson prevents the same mistake from happening again.
#
# Format: LESSON: <what went wrong> → <what to do instead>

LESSON: Git CRLF config causes merge failures on Windows → Always run `git config core.autocrlf false` in the worktree before committing. Or add a .gitattributes with `* text=auto eol=lf`.

LESSON: Mechanic output wrapped in markdown fences breaks file writes → Strip ```language and ``` lines from model output before writing to file.

LESSON: start.js using ES module import syntax but package.json missing "type": "module" → Either use require() syntax or ensure package.json has "type": "module".

LESSON: TypeScript with node: imports needs types: ['node'] in tsconfig.json and @types/node in devDependencies → Always include both when creating a Node.js TypeScript MCP server.

